155
00:10:04,442 --> 00:10:05,636
Fuck!

156
00:11:00,365 --> 00:11:03,766
The carpentry shop is gone. I don't
even know if he worked there or not...

157
00:11:03,968 --> 00:11:07,062
...but if he did, maybe he used
to come in here for hardware.

158
00:11:07,271 --> 00:11:09,364
I don't recognize him. Sorry.

159
00:11:09,574 --> 00:11:12,202
Well, I had to start somewhere.

160
00:11:12,944 --> 00:11:18,246
I'm no detective, but 1966, I would
have started at a retirement home.

161
00:11:25,256 --> 00:11:26,723
This is Brännlund's kid.

162
00:11:26,924 --> 00:11:29,085
Do you know where I might find him?
The son?

163
00:11:29,293 --> 00:11:31,659
Next to his father at the cemetery.

164
00:11:31,896 --> 00:11:36,128
